Countries are now expected to embark on plans to procure and deliver the vaccines to protect their citizens through mass immunization campaigns.Open dialogue intervention by engaging policy makers and trusted community leaders about the cost-benefit analysis of vaccines and how this correlates with development. A year ago, the first case of Covid-19 was reported in Wuhan, China. Sooner, the novel coronavirus seeped into every corner of the globe. As of this writing, over 1.6 million people have died, while more than 71 million have been infected.
Interestingly, the pandemic’s first anniversary coincides with the announcement of several vaccine candidates that have proved to be effective against the virus. Countries are now expected to embark on plans to procure and deliver the vaccines to protect their citizens through mass immunization campaigns. Vaccines have been heralded as one of the exciting and most cost-effective developments in public health.



